<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirkaldy" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Rheumatogonus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rheumatogonus luzonicus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luzonicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Rheumatogonus luzonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kirkaldy, 1909) (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkaldy, G. W." journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="389 - 390" refId="B5982226" refString="Kirkaldy, G. W., 1909. Hemiptera, old and new, No. 2. The Canadian Entomologist 41: 389 - 390" title="Hemiptera, old and new, No. 2" volume="41" year="1909">Kirkaldy 1909</bibRefCitation>
) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F5979086" captionText="Figure 9. Selected habitus illustrations of Gerromorpha of Mindoro A. Limnogonus nitidus; B. Limnometra nigripennis nigripennis; C. Tenagogonus sp. (mutilated specimen); D. Rheumatogonus luzonicus; E. Metrocoris tenuicornis. Scale bars 10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467156" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">9</figureCitation>
D) is endemic to the Philippines and has been recorded from Luzon, Mindanao, Mindoro (
<bibRefCitation author="Freitag, Hendrik" journalOrPublisher="Philippine Scientist" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="126 - 172" refId="B5979134" refString="Freitag, Hendrik, Pangantihon, Clister V, 2010. Aquatic Coleoptera and Heteroptera of the Lake Naujan National Park, Oriental Mindoro, the Philippines. Philippine Scientist 47: 126 - 172" title="Aquatic Coleoptera and Heteroptera of the Lake Naujan National Park, Oriental Mindoro, the Philippines" volume="47" year="2010">Freitag and Pangantihon 2010</bibRefCitation>
, see Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F5979090" captionText="Figure 8. Distribution of the collecting sites of Gerromorpha material (part 2) treated in this study." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467248" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">8</figureCitation>
for additional records), Negros and Panay (
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, P. P." journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="371 - 409" refId="B5978719" refString="Chen, P. P., Nieser, N., 2002. Taxonomic characters of the male endosomal structure in the genus Rheumatogonus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Gerridae), with descriptions of four new species from Borneo and Sri Lanka. Zoologische Mededelingen 76: 371 - 409" title="Taxonomic characters of the male endosomal structure in the genus Rheumatogonus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Gerridae), with descriptions of four new species from Borneo and Sri Lanka" volume="76" year="2002">Chen and Nieser 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Some unpublished records from Catanduanes, Marinduque, Sibuyan, Ticao, Cebu, Samar, Leyte, Mindanao, Siquijor and Poro have also been recognised belonging to this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Zettel, H." journalOrPublisher="Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Oesterreichischer Entomologen" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="85 - 140" refId="B5979710" refString="Zettel, H., 2014. Annotated catalogue of semi-aquatic bugs (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha) of Luzon Island, the Philippines, with descriptions of new species. Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Oesterreichischer Entomologen 66: 85 - 140" title="Annotated catalogue of semi-aquatic bugs (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha) of Luzon Island, the Philippines, with descriptions of new species" volume="66" year="2014">Zettel 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
For identification, refer to 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, P. P." journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="371 - 409" refId="B5978719" refString="Chen, P. P., Nieser, N., 2002. Taxonomic characters of the male endosomal structure in the genus Rheumatogonus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Gerridae), with descriptions of four new species from Borneo and Sri Lanka. Zoologische Mededelingen 76: 371 - 409" title="Taxonomic characters of the male endosomal structure in the genus Rheumatogonus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Gerridae), with descriptions of four new species from Borneo and Sri Lanka" volume="76" year="2002">Chen and Nieser (2002)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Habitat</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
The specimens were collected from the surface and littoral of calm and moderately fast flowing creeks and medium-sized rivers (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F5978773" captionText="Figure 1. Sampling sites at northern Mindoro (Baco, Puerto Galera). A. the first author sampling at site 396; B. Tagbinai Malaki River (305); C. Tukunan River at &quot; Hidden Paradise &quot; (303); D. lower Dulangan River (356)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/434061" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">1</figureCitation>
A, B). In general, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Rheumatogonus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rheumatogonus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Rheumatogonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kirkaldy, 1909 species inhabit mountain streams, creeks and waterfalls in the Oriental Region, specifically the shaded, steady slow-lotic sections of such watercourses (
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, P. P." journalOrPublisher="The aquatic and semi-aquatic bugs (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha &amp; Gerromorpha) of Malesia." pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" refId="B5978737" refString="Chen, P. P., Nieser, N., Zettel, H., 2005. . The aquatic and semi-aquatic bugs (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha &amp; Gerromorpha) of Malesia. Volume 5" volume="Volume 5" year="2005">Chen et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
